Import Intent Data to a Bot

Importing Intent Data is a simple way to add utterances into your bot. You can only upload intent data to dialogs with Intent Enabled, which creates an intent name to relate to the utterances.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Einstein Bots is available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience. Setup for Einstein Bots is available in Lightning Experience.
Available in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To build and manage Einstein Bots:
Customize Application
OR
Modify Metadata
OR
Manage Bots

To manage intent sets and bot training:
Customize Application
OR
Modify Metadata
OR
Manage Bots
OR
Manage Bot Training Data

To enable intents for a dialog, click Enable Dialog Intent.

Create a three-column CSV file with the headers: MlDomainName, MlIntentName, and Utterance. When uploading directly to a bot, MIDomainName refers to the bot API name and MIIntentName refers to the dialog API name.

Log into Data Loader, select Intent Utterance as the Object, and click Browse to select your CSV file.
To map your fields to MIDomainName, MIIntentName, and Utterance, click Map Fields. Click Next.
Select a directory to save your success and error files. Click Finish.
